Johannesburg – Pop Bottles is returning, with the first instalment starting in the first quarter of 2023. Event experts Rusco Experiential, in partnership with the family of the late South African artist, producer and entertainment entrepreneur Tumi ‘DJ Dimplez’ Mooi, announced the return of the lifestyle event on Thursday. “Taking it back to its genesis, the authentic Sunday gathering, aimed at young adults celebrating success and positive living, is back,” said Rusco Experiential. The first of the 2023 series will take place in Johannesburg. The date has yet to be announced. Pop Bottles is best known for its hip hop and house playlists, but will now also include trending music genres like amapiano and Afrobeats, according to the agency. Limited tickets go on sale at the end of February, when the line-up will be announced. The Star